1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:42,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:42,689 --> 00:00:43,715
[This drama is a work of fiction.]

3
00:00:43,715 --> 00:00:44,747
[Any resemblance to real persons,
places, or events is coincidental.]

4
00:00:44,747 --> 00:00:45,788
[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

5
00:00:45,788 --> 00:00:47,629
[under professional supervision.]

6
00:00:47,629 --> 00:00:49,627
[Episode 7]
Police have reclassified

7
00:00:49,627 --> 00:00:51,730
Mr. Park's death as a homicide
and are continuing their investigation,

8
00:00:51,730 --> 00:00:55,987
but with no suspect identified,
the investigation is expected to drag on.

9
00:00:55,987 --> 00:00:58,537
Meanwhile,
as the truth behind the case comes to light,

10
00:00:58,537 --> 00:01:01,102
netizens are calling for
reflection on the media's witch hunt

11
00:01:01,102 --> 00:01:07,678
and are expressing support and encouragement
for Bang Tae Seop and Chu Sang Ah.

12
00:01:17,198 --> 00:01:20,222
You know we trusted you and waited, right?

13
00:01:20,222 --> 00:01:22,062
I'm glad it all worked out.

14
00:01:22,062 --> 00:01:25,232
Thank you. It's all thanks to you.

15
00:01:34,558 --> 00:01:37,435
Bang Tae Seop, Bang Tae Seop!

16
00:01:37,435 --> 00:01:40,325
Bang Tae Seop, Bang Tae Seop!

17
00:01:40,325 --> 00:01:45,419
Bang Tae Seop, Bang Tae Seop!

18
00:01:45,419 --> 00:01:50,602
[Bang Tae Seop Secures
Changjo Party Nomination for Dongnam-gap]

19
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,840
What's all that?

20
00:02:00,840 --> 00:02:04,009
- Here, take it.
- What is it?

21
00:02:04,009 --> 00:02:07,902
I picked some out for your wife
and daughter too.

22
00:02:11,589 --> 00:02:14,093
You've been through a lot.

23
00:02:14,093 --> 00:02:17,319
It was nothing.

24
00:02:17,319 --> 00:02:20,700
Things aren't going to get any easier.

25
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:24,300
So hang in there a little longer.

26
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:26,056
Thank you.

27
00:02:26,056 --> 00:02:28,377
Let's get through it together.

28
00:02:28,377 --> 00:02:30,734
Now that things have settled a bit,

29
00:02:30,734 --> 00:02:34,543
doing a drama right away might be tough.

30
00:02:34,543 --> 00:02:37,994
The scripts that came in
have all been canceled too.

31
00:02:37,994 --> 00:02:39,238
Yeah.

32
00:02:39,238 --> 00:02:43,435
I think I need some time
before going back to TV.

33
00:02:43,435 --> 00:02:46,240
I want to ease back in with a film first.

34
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,437
Right.

35
00:02:47,437 --> 00:02:51,277
I was worried even Four Seasons
might get canceled,

36
00:02:51,277 --> 00:02:53,153
but Director Park said
he wants you no matter what.

37
00:02:53,153 --> 00:02:55,901
They were the ones who set up today's meeting.

38
00:02:55,901 --> 00:02:57,265
But are you sure about this?

39
00:02:57,265 --> 00:03:00,918
You said the script's pretty intense,
with some revealing scenes.

40
00:03:00,918 --> 00:03:03,421
You know, this isn't the time to hold back.

41
00:03:03,421 --> 00:03:09,036
It's a bold script, but if it lands,
it could even win awards.

42
00:03:09,036 --> 00:03:11,780
Yeah... It's not the end of the road.

43
00:03:11,780 --> 00:03:13,477
Let's go.

44
00:03:13,477 --> 00:03:15,827
Oh, just a moment.

45
00:03:15,827 --> 00:03:17,871
Hello, sir.

46
00:03:17,871 --> 00:03:20,013
We're on our way...

47
00:03:20,013 --> 00:03:21,998
Yeah?

48
00:03:21,998 --> 00:03:24,599
What?

49
00:03:26,786 --> 00:03:30,806
Wait, how can you do this?

50
00:03:32,695 --> 00:03:36,259
The investor suddenly changed...

51
00:03:36,259 --> 00:03:37,923
[Four Seasons]
And without the budget,

52
00:03:37,923 --> 00:03:39,264
we can't move forward with the project.

53
00:03:39,264 --> 00:03:40,583
Something feels off.

54
00:03:40,583 --> 00:03:43,576
There was nothing we could do.

55
00:04:13,347 --> 00:04:15,197
What did they say?

56
00:04:15,197 --> 00:04:17,610
Well...

57
00:04:17,610 --> 00:04:21,394
This film's aimed at festivals,
so it's not exactly commercial.

58
00:04:21,394 --> 00:04:26,707
They'd been struggling to secure funding,
but a main investor just came in today.

59
00:04:26,707 --> 00:04:30,261
The catch is...

60
00:04:30,261 --> 00:04:33,061
They want a casting change.

61
00:04:33,061 --> 00:04:36,845
Director Park said he really wanted you,

62
00:04:36,845 --> 00:04:41,125
but the investor threatened to
pull out if they didn't replace you.

63
00:04:42,716 --> 00:04:44,900
He said he's sorry.

64
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:48,123
Who's the investor?

65
00:04:48,753 --> 00:04:51,459
WR.

66
00:04:52,578 --> 00:04:55,658
Director Lee Yang Mi.

67
00:05:01,569 --> 00:05:02,949
Thank you.

68
00:05:02,949 --> 00:05:04,951
I'm Bang Tae Seop, Candidate No. 2.

69
00:05:04,951 --> 00:05:06,390
Thank you.

70
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:08,330
- Hang in there.
- Thanks a lot.

71
00:05:08,330 --> 00:05:11,190
I understand you grew up
in difficult circumstances.

72
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:15,347
Does that give you a different kind of resolve
as you enter politics?

73
00:05:16,150 --> 00:05:17,787
I'm well aware

74
00:05:17,787 --> 00:05:22,135
that this is about far more than
just one underdog's climb.

75
00:05:22,135 --> 00:05:24,461
I'll keep that in mind
and see it through to the very end.

76
00:05:24,461 --> 00:05:27,585
Please support Bang Tae Seop!

77
00:05:27,585 --> 00:05:30,982
My life is burning brighter now than ever.

78
00:05:30,982 --> 00:05:32,766
One, two, three.

79
00:05:32,766 --> 00:05:35,243
I'll carry this hope forward to victory.

80
00:05:35,243 --> 00:05:39,010
The choice is yours.

81
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:41,923
Please give me your support.

82
00:05:42,936 --> 00:05:45,600
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

83
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:49,611
The driving force of change is you.

84
00:05:49,611 --> 00:05:52,761
Everyone in Dongnam-gap, please vote for me.

85
00:05:52,761 --> 00:05:55,367
Thank you!

86
00:05:57,170 --> 00:06:02,634
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

87
00:06:02,634 --> 00:06:05,880
You're so amazing!

88
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:08,118
You look even better in person.

89
00:06:08,118 --> 00:06:09,786
Who's that pretty actress again?

90
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,601
- Chu Sang Ah!
- You're her husband, huh?

91
00:06:11,601 --> 00:06:15,063
Yes, I'm her husband.

92
00:06:20,748 --> 00:06:24,197
Park Hong Jip! Park Hong Jip!

93
00:06:24,197 --> 00:06:26,241
Candidate Park Hong Jip just arrived.

94
00:06:26,241 --> 00:06:30,454
Park Hong Jip! Park Hong Jip!

95
00:06:30,454 --> 00:06:34,190
Everyone, I'm Bang Tae Seop, Candidate No. 2!

96
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:38,594
Park Hong Jip! Park Hong Jip!

97
00:06:38,594 --> 00:06:43,265
Park Hong Jip! Park Hong Jip!

98
00:06:43,265 --> 00:06:44,898
[Park Hong Jip]

99
00:06:44,898 --> 00:06:48,491
The numbers haven't budged, then or now.

100
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:50,348
[Dongnam-gap Poll Standings]
What haven't we tried?

101
00:06:50,348 --> 00:06:52,905
Nothing, at least officially.

102
00:06:52,905 --> 00:06:54,249
What about unofficially?

103
00:06:54,249 --> 00:06:57,622
The biggest difference is,
we don't have any backers.

104
00:06:57,622 --> 00:07:00,127
I was going to tell you.

105
00:07:00,127 --> 00:07:03,942
WR isn't too pleased with you.

106
00:07:03,942 --> 00:07:08,689
Director Lee Yang Mi seems to be
pressuring the business side.

107
00:07:08,689 --> 00:07:13,828
That's probably why everyone we reach out to
is keeping their distance.

108
00:07:17,693 --> 00:07:22,041
We need to rethink our strategy.

109
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:24,145
Hold off on contacting anyone for now.

110
00:07:24,145 --> 00:07:26,034
Yes, sir.

111
00:07:26,034 --> 00:07:30,100
I'm so sick of Lee Yang Mi.

112
00:07:45,117 --> 00:07:49,207
She's the person who'd cut me
from the one project I needed most,

113
00:07:49,207 --> 00:07:52,930
then bankroll some film
she doesn't even care about

114
00:07:52,930 --> 00:07:58,335
just to watch me fade out
with nothing to my name.

115
00:08:02,283 --> 00:08:06,737
How far is she willing to take this?

116
00:08:06,737 --> 00:08:10,897
Not just my film.
She's cutting off your funding too.

117
00:08:10,897 --> 00:08:14,168
She wants to see us completely ruined.

118
00:08:14,168 --> 00:08:16,934
Damn it.

119
00:08:26,075 --> 00:08:28,397
This war's already started.

120
00:08:28,397 --> 00:08:30,286
I'll find a way.

121
00:08:30,286 --> 00:08:35,319
Whatever it is, don't give up on that film.

122
00:08:39,445 --> 00:08:42,435
What are you going to do?

123
00:08:42,435 --> 00:08:44,945
It's not just me.

124
00:08:44,945 --> 00:08:49,649
You left the prosecution
and fought your way here.

125
00:08:49,649 --> 00:08:53,042
This is a turning point for you too.

126
00:08:53,042 --> 00:08:57,026
These days,
you can't win an election without backing.

127
00:08:57,026 --> 00:09:00,452
I need to find another source of funding.

128
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:05,764
It's hard to find money

129
00:09:05,764 --> 00:09:09,577
that WR hasn't already touched.

130
00:09:16,646 --> 00:09:21,018
Then find someone
who's not on Lee Yang Mi's side.

131
00:09:26,087 --> 00:09:29,105
[The Past of WR's Lee Yang Mi,
Who Even Abandoned Her Current Husband]

132
00:09:29,105 --> 00:09:31,986
[Lee Yang Mi, once known as "Madam Lee"
who linked elites with celebrities]

133
00:09:36,306 --> 00:09:39,142
[TG Trading]

134
00:10:13,049 --> 00:10:15,862
Mr. Bang Tae Seop.

135
00:10:16,689 --> 00:10:21,289
I get that you need a hunting dog
to go after Lee Yang Mi,

136
00:10:21,289 --> 00:10:26,766
but what exactly makes you worth my money?

137
00:10:26,766 --> 00:10:31,309
The fact that she's going out of her way

138
00:10:31,309 --> 00:10:33,512
to cut off all my funding

139
00:10:33,512 --> 00:10:37,438
proves I'm a threat to her.

140
00:10:38,135 --> 00:10:40,774
Fair point.

141
00:10:41,575 --> 00:10:44,925
She is a bit of a psychopath.

142
00:10:44,925 --> 00:10:47,222
Once you get on her bad side,

143
00:10:47,222 --> 00:10:50,921
she'll crush you until you're nothing.

144
00:10:51,715 --> 00:10:56,079
So your mother ran a fish shop,
and your sister a hair salon?

145
00:10:56,079 --> 00:10:58,565
Yes.

146
00:10:58,565 --> 00:11:02,654
I built myself up from nothing. Just like you.

147
00:11:02,654 --> 00:11:07,522
People like us only climb higher
the more we're pushed down.

148
00:11:08,916 --> 00:11:11,407
Sounds like we've got a lot in common.

149
00:11:11,407 --> 00:11:14,627
I like you more and more.

150
00:11:19,325 --> 00:11:22,832
I'm going all the way.

151
00:11:23,989 --> 00:11:28,155
If you invest in me, you won't regret it.

152
00:11:40,161 --> 00:11:44,495
You've heard of gwaegangsal, right?

153
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:46,651
If it goes well, it's a jackpot.

154
00:11:46,651 --> 00:11:48,501
If not, you lose everything.

155
00:11:48,501 --> 00:11:51,408
A life of extremes.

156
00:11:51,408 --> 00:11:55,758
I divorced the man I loved
because he was young and broke,

157
00:11:55,758 --> 00:12:01,451
then remarried a rich man
who didn't have long to live.

158
00:12:02,262 --> 00:12:05,942
My life's been pretty extreme too, hasn't it?

159
00:12:05,942 --> 00:12:10,539
It's the fate of a man
with heavy karma reborn as a woman,

160
00:12:10,539 --> 00:12:16,002
living a man's life in a woman's body.

161
00:12:16,002 --> 00:12:20,045
Lonely and solitary, but exceptionally capable.

162
00:12:20,045 --> 00:12:21,763
Wherever you go,

163
00:12:21,763 --> 00:12:25,852
you'll rise to the top
and become a powerful figure.

164
00:12:25,852 --> 00:12:28,869
Oh please, power or not,

165
00:12:28,869 --> 00:12:32,342
I think I deserve a break now.

166
00:12:33,921 --> 00:12:35,738
Still,

167
00:12:35,738 --> 00:12:38,662
I've got a president to make.

168
00:12:38,662 --> 00:12:40,212
Shall we go?

169
00:12:40,212 --> 00:12:42,742
Let's go.

170
00:12:58,728 --> 00:13:01,422
Are you okay?

171
00:13:02,675 --> 00:13:05,341
Let's keep going.

172
00:13:05,341 --> 00:13:08,774
If it gets too much, let me know.

173
00:13:42,260 --> 00:13:44,813
That's it.

174
00:13:44,813 --> 00:13:47,790
The home of Assemblyman Son I told you about.

175
00:13:47,790 --> 00:13:49,740
What do you think?

176
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:51,380
Does it have the kind of energy

177
00:13:51,380 --> 00:13:55,053
that could produce a king?

178
00:13:55,053 --> 00:13:57,850
Judging by the energy of the site,

179
00:13:57,850 --> 00:14:00,094
if the timing aligns,

180
00:14:00,094 --> 00:14:03,054
it's a place where one could ride
the rising dragon's momentum

181
00:14:03,054 --> 00:14:06,157
and ascend.

182
00:14:06,891 --> 00:14:08,911
I know how to read faces.

183
00:14:08,911 --> 00:14:10,253
[Son Guk Won]

184
00:14:10,253 --> 00:14:12,031
A wood-dominant type.

185
00:14:12,031 --> 00:14:14,056
What they call a viper's face.

186
00:14:14,056 --> 00:14:17,707
Cold temperament, volatile emotions,

187
00:14:17,707 --> 00:14:20,765
and strike the wrong nerve, he bites.

188
00:14:20,765 --> 00:14:23,572
My reading's right, isn't it?

189
00:14:23,572 --> 00:14:25,096
Right.

190
00:14:25,096 --> 00:14:26,613
Based on his fortune,

191
00:14:26,613 --> 00:14:30,019
he's entering a powerful cycle
with strong backing.

192
00:14:30,019 --> 00:14:31,851
Politically, his luck is exceptional.

193
00:14:31,851 --> 00:14:35,291
He has a high chance of becoming president.

194
00:14:35,291 --> 00:14:38,538
Sounds like he's got it all.

195
00:14:38,538 --> 00:14:43,091
So, Son Guk Won is our pick
for the next presidency?

196
00:14:43,091 --> 00:14:46,339
Everything looks favorable, but...

197
00:14:46,339 --> 00:14:48,804
his lineage lacks virtue.

198
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:49,869
In a presidential race,

199
00:14:49,869 --> 00:14:52,554
the most important factor is
the candidates' ancestral graves.

200
00:14:52,554 --> 00:14:57,287
Elections are battles between ancestors.

201
00:14:58,703 --> 00:15:00,387
If my ancestors lack virtue,

202
00:15:00,387 --> 00:15:03,787
then I'll cut off someone else's ancestral ties
to make a king.

203
00:15:03,787 --> 00:15:07,665
That's how someone like me survives.

204
00:15:09,133 --> 00:15:11,030
If I can't have it,

205
00:15:11,030 --> 00:15:14,172
I'll break it.

206
00:15:19,675 --> 00:15:22,199
I'll lay out the alignment for a young tiger

207
00:15:22,199 --> 00:15:24,906
who can cut off the opposing candidate's energy

208
00:15:24,906 --> 00:15:29,646
and make Son Guk Won king.

209
00:15:29,646 --> 00:15:32,900
Let's find the one whose fate fits,

210
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:35,890
the tiger who'll be his right hand.

211
00:15:35,890 --> 00:15:38,793
Let's find him.

212
00:15:38,793 --> 00:15:41,046
Let's see.

213
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:52,033
I hear they're flipping the casting again
on Four Seasons.

214
00:15:52,033 --> 00:15:54,130
What are you talking about?

215
00:15:54,130 --> 00:15:56,281
I got a call from the producer.

216
00:15:56,281 --> 00:16:00,993
Director Lee said in a meeting
she's willing to reconsider your casting.

217
00:16:01,906 --> 00:16:03,124
What?

218
00:16:03,124 --> 00:16:04,884
You know it's got nudity,

219
00:16:04,884 --> 00:16:07,930
and it wasn't an easy role
to cast to begin with.

220
00:16:07,930 --> 00:16:10,454
Now that other actresses
have all turned it down,

221
00:16:10,454 --> 00:16:13,770
I guess they're having second thoughts.

222
00:16:13,770 --> 00:16:15,873
So the producer carefully asked

223
00:16:15,873 --> 00:16:18,877
if you'd be willing to meet

224
00:16:18,877 --> 00:16:20,818
Director Lee yourself...

225
00:16:20,818 --> 00:16:23,118
Do you even understand what's going on?

226
00:16:23,118 --> 00:16:24,954
If I want that film,

227
00:16:24,954 --> 00:16:28,067
she's telling me to come crawling back to her.

228
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:30,724
It might not mean that.

229
00:16:30,724 --> 00:16:33,081
It could just be a gesture,

230
00:16:33,081 --> 00:16:34,473
like trying to make peace over your friendship.

231
00:16:34,473 --> 00:16:37,143
"Friendship?"

232
00:16:37,143 --> 00:16:40,973
You and Director Lee used to drink together...

233
00:16:40,973 --> 00:16:42,413
Then and now,

234
00:16:42,413 --> 00:16:45,157
we were never equals.

235
00:16:45,157 --> 00:16:47,041
She toyed with me like a cat with a mouse,

236
00:16:47,041 --> 00:16:52,043
and the moment she got bored,
she could've crushed me.

237
00:16:52,043 --> 00:16:56,230
So you're just going to
let her swallow you whole?

238
00:16:57,711 --> 00:16:59,227
Yeah,

239
00:16:59,227 --> 00:17:01,621
that's how it is for actors.

240
00:17:01,621 --> 00:17:04,378
You only survive if people like her cast you,

241
00:17:04,378 --> 00:17:07,076
and you only shine
when you're in front of the camera.

242
00:17:07,076 --> 00:17:09,342
But...

243
00:17:10,525 --> 00:17:12,808
do you know

244
00:17:12,808 --> 00:17:16,994
why I took your hand when you asked me
to start a company with you

245
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:21,644
instead of staying at my old agency?

246
00:17:23,367 --> 00:17:24,939
Because

247
00:17:24,939 --> 00:17:26,568
I thought you'd be the one

248
00:17:26,568 --> 00:17:29,525
to take it all,
the roles and people like her included.

249
00:17:29,525 --> 00:17:32,555
I believed you could reach
the very top as an actress.

250
00:17:32,555 --> 00:17:34,111
And I wanted

251
00:17:34,111 --> 00:17:38,437
to be there to see it, as your manager.

252
00:17:45,084 --> 00:17:47,603
Sang Ah,

253
00:17:49,886 --> 00:17:52,913
I'll be honest with you.

254
00:17:52,913 --> 00:17:55,967
If you miss this project,

255
00:17:55,967 --> 00:18:01,567
you might be out for the rest of the year,
maybe even longer.

256
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:06,515
And if you're lucky enough
to come back in a weekend drama,

257
00:18:06,515 --> 00:18:10,159
you'll end up playing
a divorced woman or some mom role.

258
00:18:10,159 --> 00:18:13,679
You know what comes next.

259
00:18:17,597 --> 00:18:22,157
The choice is yours.

260
00:18:53,893 --> 00:18:55,950
Yeah.

261
00:18:55,950 --> 00:18:58,437
I like this mood tonight.

262
00:18:58,437 --> 00:19:01,237
A fight...

263
00:19:01,990 --> 00:19:04,534
is exhausting.

264
00:19:04,534 --> 00:19:07,180
Brutally.

265
00:19:50,044 --> 00:19:52,935
[How about a drink at your usual spot?
I'll have a table ready]

266
00:19:53,710 --> 00:19:55,593
Darn it.

267
00:19:55,593 --> 00:19:59,453
Do I look like a pushover?

268
00:20:01,989 --> 00:20:04,615
No, no.

269
00:20:07,729 --> 00:20:11,176
Would leaving it on read piss her off more?

270
00:20:24,578 --> 00:20:29,084
My taste really is oldies but goodies!

271
00:21:28,435 --> 00:21:33,576
[I'm already here]

272
00:22:31,295 --> 00:22:36,142
Sang Ah, we can't keep the table much longer...

273
00:22:46,390 --> 00:22:49,564
Actually, I only got involved

274
00:22:49,564 --> 00:22:52,557
with Lee Yang Mi for connections,

275
00:22:52,557 --> 00:22:56,663
but I did love her.

276
00:22:57,622 --> 00:23:01,295
She's got her charm. Bold, too.

277
00:23:11,731 --> 00:23:14,367
I loved her that much,

278
00:23:14,367 --> 00:23:18,473
which is why I clawed my way up here
for revenge.

279
00:23:19,123 --> 00:23:22,046
Standing next to a woman like that,
flashy and ambitious,

280
00:23:22,046 --> 00:23:23,546
isn't easy.

281
00:23:23,546 --> 00:23:27,172
She doesn't even treat men like men.

282
00:23:27,927 --> 00:23:31,347
So what about Chu Sang Ah?

283
00:23:32,041 --> 00:23:35,165
My wife respects me.

284
00:23:35,165 --> 00:23:38,608
She supports me.

285
00:23:38,608 --> 00:23:41,953
No, not that.

286
00:23:41,953 --> 00:23:44,686
Is she good to you

287
00:23:45,466 --> 00:23:48,026
in that way?

288
00:23:50,980 --> 00:23:54,520
Sir, that's...

289
00:23:55,317 --> 00:23:57,783
Oppa!

290
00:23:58,677 --> 00:24:00,406
Come on, hurry up.

291
00:24:00,406 --> 00:24:02,053
Okay.

292
00:24:03,201 --> 00:24:05,402
Hey, let's go.

293
00:24:05,402 --> 00:24:08,101
You know what?

294
00:24:08,101 --> 00:24:12,096
I get plenty of calls asking for sponsorship.

295
00:24:12,096 --> 00:24:16,951
You know why I agreed to meet you?

296
00:24:21,698 --> 00:24:24,209
Actually,

297
00:24:24,209 --> 00:24:27,722
Chu Sang Ah was my first love.

298
00:24:30,824 --> 00:24:33,494
After Lee Yang Mi tossed me aside,

299
00:24:33,494 --> 00:24:37,154
I couldn't get it up for years.

300
00:24:37,154 --> 00:24:41,824
Then I saw Chu Sang Ah's debut film...

301
00:24:41,824 --> 00:24:45,410
I couldn't sleep a wink after that.

302
00:24:48,334 --> 00:24:52,010
Answer me one thing,

303
00:24:52,010 --> 00:24:55,130
and the money's yours.

304
00:25:02,068 --> 00:25:04,779
Lend her to me

305
00:25:04,779 --> 00:25:08,122
for just one night.

306
00:26:02,967 --> 00:26:05,067
Bang Tae Seop.

307
00:26:05,067 --> 00:26:08,287
Pull yourself together.

308
00:26:09,614 --> 00:26:12,783
Get a grip...

309
00:26:12,783 --> 00:26:15,816
Get your head straight.

310
00:26:16,738 --> 00:26:19,109
Pull yourself together.

311
00:26:19,109 --> 00:26:22,209
Pull yourself together.

312
00:26:28,749 --> 00:26:31,762
- We're closing now...
- Sorry, sir.

313
00:26:31,762 --> 00:26:35,668
- Just ten more minutes please.
- All right.

314
00:26:47,603 --> 00:26:52,069
Track Lee Yang Mi's entire schedule
for the next week.

315
00:26:54,025 --> 00:26:58,100
You've got an email from Shaman Moon.

316
00:26:58,100 --> 00:27:01,725
I'm passing it along.

317
00:27:01,725 --> 00:27:06,461
If you leave it there,
how am I supposed to reach it?

318
00:27:06,461 --> 00:27:08,734
Sorry.

319
00:27:17,202 --> 00:27:19,542
Let's see...

320
00:27:19,542 --> 00:27:24,488
Who's our little tiger going to be?

321
00:27:55,672 --> 00:27:58,251
Sir.

322
00:28:03,144 --> 00:28:06,123
My wife and I...

323
00:28:06,957 --> 00:28:10,270
We're in a sexless marriage.

324
00:28:18,460 --> 00:28:21,006
That's rich.

325
00:28:29,237 --> 00:28:30,815
Come on,

326
00:28:30,815 --> 00:28:33,675
make it more interesting.

327
00:28:50,972 --> 00:28:54,510
Let's find the one whose fate fits,

328
00:28:54,510 --> 00:28:58,576
the tiger who'll be his right hand.

329
00:29:03,974 --> 00:29:08,623
[Bang Tae Seop / Male]

330
00:29:14,980 --> 00:29:17,467
Bottoms up!

331
00:29:19,707 --> 00:29:22,960
CEO Jang!

332
00:29:27,139 --> 00:29:32,712
I'll give you my heart!

333
00:29:35,116 --> 00:29:37,254
Sir!

334
00:29:37,254 --> 00:29:43,007
I'm going all the way to the end!

335
00:31:08,263 --> 00:31:11,393
Pull over for a second.

336
00:31:13,215 --> 00:31:16,095
What? Why?

337
00:31:36,062 --> 00:31:39,310
[Rising Star Hwang Jeong Won
Cast as Lead in Four Seasons]

338
00:31:43,425 --> 00:31:46,342
[A breakout rookie who beat 2,000 to 1 odds]

339
00:32:00,273 --> 00:32:02,689
Director Park Chi Young's new film

340
00:32:02,689 --> 00:32:05,326
Four Seasons has been making waves
since auditions,

341
00:32:05,326 --> 00:32:07,706
as a bold two-female-lead melodrama.

342
00:32:07,706 --> 00:32:12,160
All eyes are now on rising newcomer
Hwang Jeong Won,

343
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:16,521
- Great.
- who landed the role against 2,000 to 1 odds.

344
00:32:19,043 --> 00:32:21,342
Good.

345
00:32:25,734 --> 00:32:28,121
Good.

346
00:32:36,213 --> 00:32:38,030
- Ms. Yoon So Young.
- Yes.

347
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:40,880
Right this way, please.

348
00:32:46,522 --> 00:32:51,449
That punk used to get drunk
and beat me like a maniac.

349
00:32:51,449 --> 00:32:55,181
He even threw away his own child.

350
00:32:55,787 --> 00:32:58,587
Because of that,

351
00:32:58,587 --> 00:33:00,458
I've been dragged down my whole life.

352
00:33:00,458 --> 00:33:03,576
You've seen me hit rock bottom
with your own eyes.

353
00:33:03,576 --> 00:33:07,602
And now you're talking about forgiveness?

354
00:33:12,162 --> 00:33:15,415
That's as far as my patience goes.

355
00:33:16,845 --> 00:33:20,391
Stay out of my life.

356
00:33:32,626 --> 00:33:35,977
Jeong Won, I hear you have a role model.

357
00:33:35,977 --> 00:33:41,190
I've admired actress Chu Sang Ah
since I was young.

358
00:33:41,190 --> 00:33:46,343
If I get the chance, I'd love to work with her.

359
00:33:50,809 --> 00:33:54,388
The role you were originally up
for in Four Seasons...

360
00:33:54,388 --> 00:33:57,654
she's playing your counterpart.

361
00:34:00,209 --> 00:34:03,494
I also heard the production noticed
Hwang Jeong Won

362
00:34:03,494 --> 00:34:07,794
when she stood in for you,
and then recommended her to WR.

363
00:34:08,941 --> 00:34:11,536
The fact that she picked her of all people...

364
00:34:11,536 --> 00:34:13,823
I really can't tell what Director Lee is up to.

365
00:34:13,823 --> 00:34:16,457
[Suspect in the murder of Mr. Park
identified as a man in his 30s]

366
00:34:21,731 --> 00:34:24,934
[Initially believed to be a woman
in her 20s based on eyewitness descriptions]

367
00:34:24,934 --> 00:34:26,934
[later corrected to a male suspect]

368
00:34:42,092 --> 00:34:44,137
Okay, got it.

369
00:34:44,137 --> 00:34:47,790
[The Start of Change! A New Dongnam]
[No. 2, Bang Tae Seop]

370
00:34:59,997 --> 00:35:02,027
[Transfer from CEO Jang completed]

371
00:35:08,668 --> 00:35:11,615
Yeah, what happened?

372
00:35:11,615 --> 00:35:14,052
Well... right after the incident,

373
00:35:14,052 --> 00:35:16,177
we identified the suspect
as the woman seen on CCTV

374
00:35:16,177 --> 00:35:17,684
and proceeded with the investigation.

375
00:35:17,684 --> 00:35:22,219
But we later found signs
the victim had a struggle with the attacker,

376
00:35:22,219 --> 00:35:26,886
and fiber analysis from the victim's skin
showed traces from clothing

377
00:35:26,886 --> 00:35:31,387
sold only in big-and-tall sizes
for men over 185 centimeters.

378
00:35:31,387 --> 00:35:36,784
We also received a witness tip
about a man seen near the motel,

379
00:35:36,784 --> 00:35:39,248
and secured additional dashcam footage.

380
00:35:39,248 --> 00:35:40,841
At this point,

381
00:35:40,841 --> 00:35:44,780
it's unlikely the suspect is that woman.

382
00:35:46,799 --> 00:35:48,716
Oh, thank you.

383
00:35:48,716 --> 00:35:51,182
- Hello.
- Welcome.

384
00:35:51,182 --> 00:35:54,353
Chu Sang Ah! Chu Sang Ah!

385
00:35:54,353 --> 00:35:57,463
Chu Sang Ah! Chu Sang Ah!

386
00:35:57,463 --> 00:35:59,150
Chu Sang Ah...

387
00:35:59,150 --> 00:36:00,914
Chu Sang Ah!

388
00:36:00,914 --> 00:36:03,763
Thank you for your hard work.

389
00:36:09,819 --> 00:36:12,602
You thought

390
00:36:12,602 --> 00:36:15,572
Hwang Jeong Won killed Park Jae Sang too,

391
00:36:15,572 --> 00:36:18,362
didn't you?

392
00:36:25,443 --> 00:36:29,327
I know you sent her to tail me,

393
00:36:29,327 --> 00:36:32,453
so just tell me everything.

394
00:36:38,109 --> 00:36:42,943
I've known her since she was young,
from a case I handled early on.

395
00:36:42,943 --> 00:36:47,343
It was self-defense against someone
who barely deserved to be called human.

396
00:36:47,343 --> 00:36:50,140
She was smart, reckless, and desperate.

397
00:36:50,140 --> 00:36:53,873
That's why I gave her a few jobs.

398
00:36:56,266 --> 00:36:59,177
She showed up on CCTV,
so I had to consider her a suspect,

399
00:36:59,177 --> 00:37:02,223
but I hoped it wasn't her.

400
00:37:04,490 --> 00:37:07,168
Now that they've identified a suspect,

401
00:37:07,168 --> 00:37:10,677
once he's in custody, we'll know soon enough.

402
00:37:17,966 --> 00:37:21,269
Lee Yang Mi reached out.

403
00:37:21,269 --> 00:37:24,897
There were things I needed to dig into
about the film and Hwang Jeong Won,

404
00:37:24,897 --> 00:37:27,058
so I met with her.

405
00:37:27,058 --> 00:37:28,701
Come work with me.

406
00:37:28,701 --> 00:37:32,063
I'll plug you into Assemblyman Son's line.

407
00:37:32,063 --> 00:37:34,706
The money you got from CEO Jang
and the Changjo Party situation...

408
00:37:34,706 --> 00:37:37,470
I'll take care of it, so don't worry.

409
00:37:37,470 --> 00:37:41,333
So now you want your enemy on the inside?

410
00:37:41,333 --> 00:37:44,003
Nothing that dramatic.

411
00:37:44,003 --> 00:37:47,683
Let's just say my stance has changed.

412
00:37:48,523 --> 00:37:51,127
That fortune-teller you've been seeing...

413
00:37:51,127 --> 00:37:54,447
Shaman Moon, right?

414
00:37:56,712 --> 00:38:01,259
You're quick with the gossip.
You really are a natural politician.

415
00:38:01,259 --> 00:38:03,019
That's a shame.

416
00:38:03,019 --> 00:38:04,382
After the election,

417
00:38:04,382 --> 00:38:09,007
I'm planning to align with
Assemblyman Gu Hong Seo.

418
00:38:09,007 --> 00:38:11,977
Gu Hong Seo? That connection won't last.

419
00:38:11,977 --> 00:38:14,227
I'm backing Son Guk Won,

420
00:38:14,227 --> 00:38:18,370
and there's no money in this country
that can beat WR.

421
00:38:18,370 --> 00:38:22,243
You chose your position
knowing what kind of bombs are about to go off

422
00:38:22,243 --> 00:38:25,441
around Assemblyman Son, didn't you?

423
00:38:25,441 --> 00:38:29,013
Defusing bombs is my specialty.

424
00:38:30,147 --> 00:38:31,744
Fine.

425
00:38:31,744 --> 00:38:33,768
Then put that specialty to good use.

426
00:38:33,768 --> 00:38:36,325
Let's get to why I'm here.

427
00:38:36,325 --> 00:38:39,388
Go ahead.

428
00:38:39,388 --> 00:38:42,438
Hwang Jeong Won. And that film.

429
00:38:42,438 --> 00:38:45,804
What are you really after?

430
00:38:46,635 --> 00:38:50,482
Well, isn't it interesting?

431
00:38:52,843 --> 00:38:56,067
If this is your revenge play,
keep it between us.

432
00:38:56,067 --> 00:38:59,933
Leave Sang Ah out of it.

433
00:39:00,957 --> 00:39:02,661
Exactly.

434
00:39:02,661 --> 00:39:05,145
So think it through carefully,

435
00:39:05,145 --> 00:39:07,994
Mr. Bang Tae Seop.

436
00:39:11,244 --> 00:39:12,594
So...

437
00:39:12,594 --> 00:39:14,618
did you turn her down?

438
00:39:14,618 --> 00:39:16,162
I'm holding off.

439
00:39:16,162 --> 00:39:19,574
If I say no, your film goes with it.

440
00:39:19,574 --> 00:39:21,292
You need that film, right?

441
00:39:21,292 --> 00:39:25,159
Even so, I don't want you getting involved
with her because of it.

442
00:39:25,159 --> 00:39:26,809
That won't happen.

443
00:39:26,809 --> 00:39:28,162
She came to me knowing

444
00:39:28,162 --> 00:39:30,849
I wouldn't walk away
from the election that easily.

445
00:39:30,849 --> 00:39:34,676
That means she needs me.

446
00:39:34,676 --> 00:39:36,747
Until she gets my answer,

447
00:39:36,747 --> 00:39:41,008
I'll find a way to keep her
from messing with you.

448
00:39:52,310 --> 00:39:56,083
Then I'll take the bait for now.

449
00:39:56,083 --> 00:39:58,753
I need that film,

450
00:39:58,753 --> 00:40:01,516
she needs you...

451
00:40:01,516 --> 00:40:05,462
and right now, it looks like we need her too.

452
00:40:07,346 --> 00:40:10,495
[Dongnam-gap Poll Standings]
[Bang Tae Seop 28.7%, Park Hong Jip 34.8%]

453
00:40:14,303 --> 00:40:17,860
I know exactly how far my image has fallen

454
00:40:17,860 --> 00:40:21,453
since the Park Jae Sang case.

455
00:40:21,453 --> 00:40:24,084
Elections are about image,

456
00:40:24,084 --> 00:40:28,691
and at a time when
I should be your greatest asset...

457
00:40:28,691 --> 00:40:33,930
Even with an actress for a wife,
your team won't even suggest a joint campaign.

458
00:40:35,655 --> 00:40:38,941
That hurts my pride.

459
00:40:38,941 --> 00:40:41,605
My pride's already been crushed.

460
00:40:41,605 --> 00:40:45,853
If taking another hit can turn things around,

461
00:40:45,853 --> 00:40:48,779
then so be it.

462
00:40:50,286 --> 00:40:54,952
Looks like Lee Yang Mi deliberately
let her schedule slip today.

463
00:40:57,361 --> 00:41:00,675
[Chu Sang Ah: I'll have a table ready]
[Chu Sang Ah: I'm already here]

464
00:41:04,293 --> 00:41:06,933
Was I playing too hard to get?

465
00:41:06,933 --> 00:41:10,640
She's probably putting a lot of effort
into working Son Guk Won.

466
00:41:10,640 --> 00:41:12,818
And she would've made sure it got out that

467
00:41:12,818 --> 00:41:15,613
if she wants you, she has to go through me.

468
00:41:15,613 --> 00:41:18,912
You're so amazing.

469
00:41:31,677 --> 00:41:35,850
So I'll meet her first.

470
00:41:45,320 --> 00:41:47,163
I've heard

471
00:41:47,163 --> 00:41:50,623
Bang Tae Seop is no ordinary guy.

472
00:41:51,323 --> 00:41:54,353
But with Chu Sang Ah's image already tanked,

473
00:41:54,353 --> 00:41:56,677
is she still of any use?

474
00:41:56,677 --> 00:41:58,614
A celebrity's image?

475
00:41:58,614 --> 00:42:02,054
One word from me and it flips overnight.

476
00:42:02,054 --> 00:42:04,144
I'll handle the rebuild,

477
00:42:04,144 --> 00:42:07,464
so don't worry.

478
00:42:08,290 --> 00:42:11,277
Well...

479
00:42:11,277 --> 00:42:12,821
His poll numbers, everything...

480
00:42:12,821 --> 00:42:15,621
It's all falling flat.

481
00:42:39,266 --> 00:42:42,066
Hello.

482
00:42:47,378 --> 00:42:49,020
Oh, Sang Ah.

483
00:42:49,020 --> 00:42:52,588
You haven't been golfing lately.
What brings you here?

484
00:42:52,588 --> 00:42:55,900
I came to see you, Director.

485
00:42:55,900 --> 00:42:57,779
Ms. Chu Sang Ah.

486
00:42:57,779 --> 00:43:01,425
Nice to finally meet you. I'm a fan.

487
00:43:21,554 --> 00:43:23,105
Nice to meet you.

488
00:43:23,105 --> 00:43:24,955
I've heard a lot about you too.

489
00:43:24,955 --> 00:43:28,041
Then I'll see you again.

490
00:43:29,170 --> 00:43:33,603
Get home safe. I'll be in touch.

491
00:43:36,715 --> 00:43:41,048
You're still pulling those little fox tricks,
even at your age.

492
00:44:17,468 --> 00:44:19,040
Let her in.

493
00:44:19,040 --> 00:44:21,456
Yes, ma'am.

494
00:44:33,693 --> 00:44:36,615
No manners at all.

495
00:44:39,822 --> 00:44:41,846
Director.

496
00:44:41,846 --> 00:44:45,209
You've got something to say to me, don't you?

497
00:44:45,209 --> 00:44:48,888
I think it'd be better somewhere private.

498
00:44:50,249 --> 00:44:51,879
By the way,

499
00:44:51,879 --> 00:44:56,398
you look rough.

500
00:44:56,398 --> 00:44:59,958
Must've been a lot to deal with.

501
00:45:01,172 --> 00:45:03,592
Thanks to you.

502
00:45:03,592 --> 00:45:05,535
Yeah.

503
00:45:05,535 --> 00:45:09,412
Hwang Jeong Won...
she used to be your stand-in actor, huh?

504
00:45:09,412 --> 00:45:12,030
Just a stand-in,

505
00:45:12,030 --> 00:45:17,961
and now she shows up as the lead
in the film you wanted so badly.

506
00:45:17,961 --> 00:45:22,462
That's better drama than anything on screen.

507
00:45:23,912 --> 00:45:26,142
Yeah.

508
00:45:26,142 --> 00:45:29,235
Like some punk you tried to crush

509
00:45:29,235 --> 00:45:32,748
ends up becoming the key player.

510
00:45:34,755 --> 00:45:37,555
Go on.

511
00:45:49,398 --> 00:45:51,642
You want Assemblyman Son in the Blue House

512
00:45:51,642 --> 00:45:55,742
so you can take over WR.

513
00:45:55,742 --> 00:45:59,129
That means you need Tae Seop, right?

514
00:45:59,129 --> 00:46:01,259
Director,

515
00:46:01,259 --> 00:46:05,285
you're the kind of person
who'd change your daughter's birth time

516
00:46:05,285 --> 00:46:06,723
over a fortune teller's word...

517
00:46:06,723 --> 00:46:12,073
even push her head back in during labor. Right?

518
00:46:12,073 --> 00:46:14,653
So?

519
00:46:19,089 --> 00:46:21,379
Give me the film you took from me.

520
00:46:21,379 --> 00:46:25,272
Make me the face of WR

521
00:46:25,272 --> 00:46:29,239
and fix the image you destroyed.

522
00:46:31,882 --> 00:46:35,515
Then I'll bring him in.

523
00:46:38,651 --> 00:46:39,690
What?

524
00:46:39,690 --> 00:46:44,157
If Bang Tae Seop and I come in
with some standing,

525
00:46:44,157 --> 00:46:46,200
that benefits you and Assemblyman Son too,

526
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:48,062
doesn't it?

527
00:46:48,062 --> 00:46:52,781
From what I saw earlier,
I think he feels the same.

528
00:47:11,503 --> 00:47:14,136
Hey.

529
00:47:14,136 --> 00:47:17,889
Do you take me for a fool?

530
00:47:19,171 --> 00:47:21,618
That aside,

531
00:47:21,618 --> 00:47:25,893
you're the one who needs my film, aren't you?

532
00:47:36,173 --> 00:47:38,540
You're right.

533
00:47:38,540 --> 00:47:41,531
I need it.

534
00:47:41,531 --> 00:47:47,242
No, not "need." Without me, you're finished.

535
00:47:47,242 --> 00:47:50,959
No one will cast you.
You'll just fade away and disappear.

536
00:47:50,959 --> 00:47:53,252
I'll just be mildly inconvenienced.

537
00:47:53,252 --> 00:47:56,353
But standing in front of someone like me,

538
00:47:56,353 --> 00:48:01,236
why do you carry yourself like this?

539
00:48:06,530 --> 00:48:09,620
What a shitty mood.

540
00:48:16,357 --> 00:48:19,917
That was my hole-in-one ball. What a waste.

541
00:49:30,212 --> 00:49:33,205
I'll wash it for you.

542
00:49:46,908 --> 00:49:48,539
But

543
00:49:48,539 --> 00:49:52,405
how am I supposed to trust you
and your husband?

544
00:49:53,042 --> 00:49:56,622
That's why I'm here as collateral.

545
00:49:57,415 --> 00:50:00,126
I don't have the will or the strength

546
00:50:00,126 --> 00:50:03,146
to fight you anymore.

547
00:50:05,864 --> 00:50:09,984
And if I can't bring in Bang Tae Seop,

548
00:50:09,984 --> 00:50:13,657
you can just cut me from the film.

549
00:50:21,888 --> 00:50:24,454
Isn't that right?

550
00:50:34,129 --> 00:50:37,449
You've gotten sharper.

551
00:50:41,307 --> 00:50:44,287
Thanks to you.

552
00:51:08,357 --> 00:51:12,270
Even when no one believed in me,

553
00:51:12,270 --> 00:51:15,577
I kept going with everything I had,

554
00:51:16,277 --> 00:51:20,136
pushing forward until I made it here.

555
00:51:37,686 --> 00:51:39,816
For the next ten years,

556
00:51:39,816 --> 00:51:44,002
I'll be right here with you.

557
00:51:57,886 --> 00:52:00,550
Oh my, she looks gorgeous.

558
00:52:00,550 --> 00:52:03,550
She hasn't changed a bit.

559
00:52:03,550 --> 00:52:07,537
Where does all that aging even go?

560
00:52:07,537 --> 00:52:08,856
I know.

561
00:52:08,856 --> 00:52:13,418
When she goes to the film festival,
she should get me a dress too.

562
00:52:15,131 --> 00:52:18,067
Look at this.

563
00:52:18,067 --> 00:52:20,200
She's such a devoted wife.

564
00:52:20,200 --> 00:52:23,287
[Chu Sang Ah to campaign in support of
her husband, candidate Bang Tae Seop]

565
00:52:23,287 --> 00:52:24,938
It's only a matter of time

566
00:52:24,938 --> 00:52:28,611
before our Candidate Bang becomes
Assemblyman Bang.

567
00:52:28,611 --> 00:52:33,134
They said I'd have the worst luck this year,
like something awful was bound to happen,

568
00:52:33,134 --> 00:52:34,598
but instead

569
00:52:34,598 --> 00:52:38,708
everything's been going my way.

570
00:52:38,708 --> 00:52:41,811
You could quit the salon now.

571
00:52:41,811 --> 00:52:43,140
Should I just quit for good?

572
00:52:43,140 --> 00:52:44,947
Go ahead, do it!

573
00:52:44,947 --> 00:52:49,814
Let's welcome Candidate Bang Tae Seop!

574
00:52:49,814 --> 00:52:52,983
It's been two days since the WR ad
and casting news featuring your wife dropped,

575
00:52:52,983 --> 00:52:55,569
and your approval rating is already up 2.4%.

576
00:52:55,569 --> 00:52:57,500
Starting with today's first joint appearance,

577
00:52:57,500 --> 00:52:59,948
[Dongnam-gap, Overall Approval Ratings]
we should keep you and your wife

578
00:52:59,948 --> 00:53:03,914
front and center through Election Day.

579
00:53:07,876 --> 00:53:09,943
[Lee Yang Mi]

580
00:53:12,098 --> 00:53:14,834
How does it feel?

581
00:53:16,238 --> 00:53:17,382
It's sweet.

582
00:53:17,382 --> 00:53:19,729
Fall off a villa, you get a few bruises.

583
00:53:19,729 --> 00:53:24,416
Fall off a high-rise, you shatter.

584
00:53:24,416 --> 00:53:26,886
I'm giving you a boost before bringing you in,

585
00:53:26,886 --> 00:53:28,496
so enjoy it while it lasts.

586
00:53:28,496 --> 00:53:30,616
Do what you need to do, then come over.

587
00:53:30,616 --> 00:53:34,456
Your deadline is the day before the election.

588
00:53:36,076 --> 00:53:37,594
I'll think it over.

589
00:53:37,594 --> 00:53:39,293
Sure.

590
00:53:39,293 --> 00:53:42,493
But don't take too long.

591
00:53:47,636 --> 00:53:51,382
Your wife has arrived.

592
00:53:54,031 --> 00:53:57,055
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

593
00:53:57,055 --> 00:54:00,881
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

594
00:54:04,476 --> 00:54:07,479
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

595
00:54:07,479 --> 00:54:10,219
Bang Tae Seop!

596
00:54:11,712 --> 00:54:14,210
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

597
00:54:14,210 --> 00:54:16,516
Chu Sang Ah! Chu Sang Ah!

598
00:54:16,516 --> 00:54:17,651
They've arrived.

599
00:54:17,651 --> 00:54:21,184
Let's welcome Candidate Bang Tae Seop.

600
00:54:21,184 --> 00:54:23,115
[I will take responsibility
for Dongnam-gap's future]

601
00:54:23,115 --> 00:54:26,025
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

602
00:54:26,025 --> 00:54:28,455
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

603
00:54:28,455 --> 00:54:32,081
Hello, I'm Bang Tae Seop.

604
00:54:35,742 --> 00:54:37,079
Bang Tae Seop!

605
00:54:37,079 --> 00:54:41,636
Seeing all of you here today...

606
00:54:41,636 --> 00:54:44,882
it brings a lot of emotions.

607
00:54:45,729 --> 00:54:51,877
Not once on the way here was the path easy,

608
00:54:51,877 --> 00:54:55,884
and I never chose the easy road.

609
00:54:55,884 --> 00:54:58,268
And now, once again,

610
00:54:58,268 --> 00:55:04,254
I'm choosing the harder path.

611
00:55:04,254 --> 00:55:06,174
In all the history of general elections,

612
00:55:06,174 --> 00:55:11,606
the Changjo Party has never won here
in Dongnam-gap.

613
00:55:11,606 --> 00:55:15,413
But I won't take the easy way into politics.

614
00:55:16,574 --> 00:55:21,943
I've endured hardship for the sake of justice,

615
00:55:21,943 --> 00:55:25,557
and together with you,

616
00:55:25,557 --> 00:55:28,817
I will change history.

617
00:55:28,817 --> 00:55:32,370
Please give me

618
00:55:32,370 --> 00:55:35,023
your support.

619
00:55:37,811 --> 00:55:40,909
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

620
00:55:40,909 --> 00:55:44,034
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

621
00:55:44,034 --> 00:55:47,084
Next, please welcome Candidate Bang's wife,

622
00:55:47,084 --> 00:55:50,330
actress Chu Sang Ah.

623
00:56:07,344 --> 00:56:10,558
Chu Sang Ah! Bang Tae Seop!

624
00:56:10,558 --> 00:56:14,571
Chu Sang Ah! Bang Tae Seop!

625
00:56:15,553 --> 00:56:20,154
We still have a long way to go,
and enemies on all sides.

626
00:56:20,154 --> 00:56:23,633
Even so, we've made it this far.

627
00:56:32,750 --> 00:56:34,774
Like before,

628
00:56:34,774 --> 00:56:38,580
this is going to turn into a battle of issues.

629
00:56:39,730 --> 00:56:45,496
That's the burden
you and I have to carry to the end.

630
00:56:46,440 --> 00:56:49,967
It won't be easy from here on out.

631
00:56:52,887 --> 00:56:55,565
We've come this far.

632
00:56:55,565 --> 00:56:58,991
What's the worst that could happen?

633
00:57:07,314 --> 00:57:09,833
Still,

634
00:57:10,726 --> 00:57:13,993
I'd rather break

635
00:57:13,993 --> 00:57:17,286
than fade away.

636
00:57:24,039 --> 00:57:27,439
That's not going to happen.

637
00:57:34,362 --> 00:57:36,486
I've got a card I've been saving.

638
00:57:36,486 --> 00:57:39,263
- Chu Sang Ah!
- Bang Tae Seop!

639
00:57:39,263 --> 00:57:42,513
- Chu Sang Ah!
- Bang Tae Seop!

640
00:57:42,513 --> 00:57:45,470
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Chu Sang Ah!

641
00:57:45,470 --> 00:57:49,516
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Chu Sang Ah!

642
00:57:50,279 --> 00:57:52,037
Bang Tae Seop!

643
00:57:52,037 --> 00:57:55,034
Bang Tae Seop! Chu Sang Ah!

644
00:57:55,034 --> 00:57:58,104
Bang Tae Seop! Chu Sang Ah!

645
00:57:58,104 --> 00:58:02,197
Bang Tae Seop! Bang Tae Seop!

646
00:58:16,683 --> 00:58:19,662
With that card,

647
00:58:20,682 --> 00:58:23,513
I'll cut

648
00:58:23,513 --> 00:58:26,639
Lee Yang Mi off at the wrist.

649
00:59:30,869 --> 00:59:34,252
I'm going to decline your offer, Director.

650
00:59:34,252 --> 00:59:36,669
What makes you think you can pull this?

651
00:59:36,669 --> 00:59:39,892
How did you get tangled up with Director Lee?

652
00:59:39,892 --> 00:59:42,216
She's someone I owe.

653
00:59:42,216 --> 00:59:46,366
I'm holding a card you can't beat,
no matter what you do.

654
00:59:46,366 --> 00:59:48,670
How long are you going to live like this?

655
00:59:48,670 --> 00:59:51,354
Don't you want out?

656
00:59:51,354 --> 00:59:52,398
Action!

657
00:59:52,398 --> 00:59:54,237
I warned you.

658
00:59:54,237 --> 00:59:58,717
The higher you climb, the harder you fall.
